  <i> are answered,</i>

01:05:12.029 --> 01:05:16.364
 <i> "you will have a windfall</i>
 <i> and be able to</i>
 <i> come and see us soon."</i>

01:05:16.366 --> 01:05:18.666
         Why does it
         always rain
         at the seaside, Daddy?

01:05:18.668 --> 01:05:24.138
                       What?
           Why does it always
           rain at the seaside?

01:05:26.041 --> 01:05:29.342
               Why does it rain
               at the seaside?

01:05:33.014 --> 01:05:36.248
        To bring the rents down
        in the hotels.

01:05:36.250 --> 01:05:37.549
                    (LAUGHING)

01:05:37.551 --> 01:05:38.283
                     Well,

01:05:38.285 --> 01:05:43.521
             you've got trouble
             with three down
             on that side,

01:05:43.523 --> 01:05:46.891
            and one over there.

01:05:46.893 --> 01:05:50.327
     We need to do very
     extensive root canal work.

01:05:50.329 --> 01:05:52.929
        Then the teeth
        will have to be capped.

01:05:53.831 --> 01:05:56.231
      How much is this
      going to cost?

01:05:56.233 --> 01:06:00.268
                  A lot.
                  About $2,500.

01:06:01.938 --> 01:06:03.137
              God!

01:06:03.139 --> 01:06:05.172
                Well, that's
                for everything.

01:06:05.174 --> 01:06:07.674
          Oh, God!

01:06:20.588 --> 01:06:21.954
            (WHIRRING)

01:06:23.757 --> 01:06:28.426
     <i> HELENE: "Dear Frankie.</i>
     <i> Trust you and Nora</i>
     <i> had a fine holiday.</i>

01:06:28.428 --> 01:06:30.661
         <i> "Mine was spent</i>
         <i> in Central Park.</i>

01:06:30.663 --> 01:06:33.797
    <i> "I had a month's vacation</i>
    <i> from Joey,</i>
    <i> my dear little dentist.</i>

01:06:33.799 --> 01:06:38.168
    <i> "He went on his honeymoon.</i>
    <i> I financed it.</i>

01:06:38.170 --> 01:06:39.402
      <i> "Did I tell you,</i>
      <i> he told me last spring</i>

01:06:39.404 --> 01:06:42.438
      <i> "I had to have</i>
      <i> all my teeth capped</i>
      <i> or all my teeth out?</i>

01:06:42.440 --> 01:06:47.543
   <i> "I decided to have them</i>
   <i> capped as I have got used</i>
   <i> to having teeth.</i>

01:06:47.545 --> 01:06:51.547
       <i> "But the cost is</i>
       <i> simply astronomical.</i>

01:06:51.549 --> 01:06:54.550
  <i> "So Elizabeth will have to</i>
  <i> ascend the throne without me.</i>

01:06:54.552 --> 01:06:59.421
<i> "Teeth are all I'm going</i>
<i> to see crowned</i>
<i> for the next couple of years."</i>

01:07:02.025 --> 01:07:04.158
              She's not coming.

01:07:06.462 --> 01:07:08.061
               Not coming?

01:07:10.465 --> 01:07:13.098
            Helene, she's not
            coming to London.

01:07:14.701 --> 01:07:17.034
               Not for
               a bit anyway.

01:08:05.751 --> 01:08:09.619
  <i> MAN ON RADIO: Today</i>
  <i> as a new chapter in history</i>
  <i> begins in Britain,</i>

01:08:09.621 --> 01:08:13.222
  <i> Pepperell presents its world</i>
  <i> famous lady Pepperell sheets,</i>

01:08:13.224 --> 01:08:17.492
      <i> in classic white</i>
      <i> and in six beautiful</i>
      <i> coronation colors.</i>

01:08:17.493 --> 01:08:22.563
      <i> Like Princess Pink,</i>
      <i> Duchess Yellow,</i>
      <i> Windsor Rose...</i>

01:08:22.564 --> 01:08:25.465
    <i> MAN ON TV: And behind them</i>
    <i> once again in procession,</i>

01:08:25.466 --> 01:08:29.068
      <i> the Prime Minister</i>
      <i> of the United Kingdom,</i>

01:08:30.270 --> 01:08:31.370
     <i> Sir Winston Churchill.</i>

01:08:31.372 --> 01:08:33.471
         Thank you.
       Sorry.

01:08:34.174 --> 01:08:37.274
      <i> And now the signal</i>
      <i> is given for a fanfare...</i>

01:08:37.277 --> 01:08:37.975
 <i> FRANK: "Dear Helene.</i>

01:08:37.977 --> 01:08:42.245
  <i> "Just a note to let you know</i>
  <i> that your parcel arrived</i>
  <i> safely on June 1,</i>

01:08:42.247 --> 01:08:45.747
  <i> "just in time for our</i>
  <i> Coronation Day celebrations.</i>

01:08:45.750 --> 01:08:48.649
   <i> "We had a number of friends</i>
   <i> at home to watch TV</i>
   <i> on the day.</i>

01:08:48.652 --> 01:08:54.389
  <i> "So the ham was most welcome</i>
  <i> to provide them</i>
  <i> with something to eat.</i>

01:08:54.390 --> 01:08:54.988
        <i> "It was delicious.</i>

01:08:54.991 --> 01:08:58.492
      <i> "We all drank your health</i>
      <i> as well as the Queen's."</i>

01:08:58.493 --> 01:08:59.392
                 Thank you,
                 Frank.

01:08:59.394 --> 01:09:01.260
 They're real ham,
 you know.

01:09:14.108 --> 01:09:18.676
  <i> (GOD SAVE THE QUEEN</i> PLAYING)

01:10:11.732 --> 01:10:14.199
  <i> (ANNOUNCER CHATTERING ON TV)</i>

01:10:26.179 --> 01:10:29.480
       <i> HELENE: "Dear Frank.</i>
       <i> I'll be obliged</i>

01:10:29.482 --> 01:10:33.383
    <i> "if you'll send Nora</i>
    <i> and the girls to church</i>
    <i> the next month</i>

01:10:33.385 --> 01:10:35.785
    <i> "to pray for the continued</i>
    <i> health and strength</i>

01:10:35.787 --> 01:10:41.824
  <i> "of Messrs. Gilliam, Reese,</i>
  <i> Snider, Campanella, Robinson,</i>

01:10:41.826 --> 01:10:43.025
   <i> "Hodges, Furillo, Podres,</i>

01:10:43.027 --> 01:10:48.597
     <i> "Newcombe and Labine,</i>
     <i> collectively known as</i>
     <i> the Brooklyn Dodgers."</i>

01:10:49.499 --> 01:10:51.966
         I'm a Dodger fan!
              I'm a Yankee fan!

01:10:51.968 --> 01:10:56.070
     <i> HELENE: "If they lose</i>
     <i> this World Series,</i>
     <i> I shall do myself in.</i>

01:10:56.072 --> 01:10:57.037
 <i> "And then where will you be?"</i>

01:10:57.039 --> 01:11:00.373
    <i> ANNOUNCER:</i>
    <i> And the Yankees still lead.</i>

01:11:00.375 --> 01:11:02.641
        MAN: Here we go,
        right down. Hey.

01:11:03.410 --> 01:11:06.677
   <i> FRANK: "Dear Helene,</i>
   <i> I shall be only too pleased</i>

01:11:06.679 --> 01:11:09.913
       <i> "to root for</i>
       <i> the Brooklyn Dodgers</i>

01:11:09.915 --> 01:11:13.983
    <i> "if you will reciprocate</i>
    <i> by a few cheers</i>
    <i> for the Spurs,</i>

01:11:13.985 --> 01:11:16.819
     <i> "the Tottenham Hotspur</i>
     <i> Football Club</i>
     <i> to the uninitiated,</i>

01:11:16.821 --> 01:11:21.957
   <i> "who are at present</i>
   <i> languishing next to</i>
   <i> the bottom of the League.</i>

01:11:21.959 --> 01:11:24.726
      <i> "However, the season</i>
      <i> does not finish</i>
      <i> until next April,</i>

01:11:24.728 --> 01:11:29.530
  <i> "so they have plenty of time</i>
  <i> to get themselves</i>
  <i> out of the mess."</i>

01:11:29.532 --> 01:11:31.431
       (PEOPLE CHEERING)

01:11:37.539 --> 01:11:38.871
              WOMAN: Excuse me.

01:11:38.873 --> 01:11:39.371
 BILL: Yes.

01:11:39.373 --> 01:11:42.507
         Do you have
         a collection of essays
         by George Orwell?

01:11:42.509 --> 01:11:43.074
 George Orwell?

01:11:43.076 --> 01:11:48.345
      The one I really
      wanted to find is
      called <i> Inside the Whale.</i>

01:11:48.347 --> 01:11:50.046
  <i> Inside the Whale?</i>
  Yeah.

01:11:50.048 --> 01:11:55.551
 I'm not sure.
 Just a moment,
 I'll have a look.

01:12:26.951 --> 01:12:29.117
 I'm so sorry.
 I haven't got a copy
 of Orwell's essays,

01:12:29.119 --> 01:12:34.222
 but I do have
 a very nice first edition
 of <i> Animal Farm.</i>

01:12:34.224 --> 01:12:36.724
             I particularly
             wanted the essays.

01:12:36.726 --> 01:12:39.793
 Perhaps, we could try
 and find them for you.

01:12:39.795 --> 01:12:40.660
                 Oh, I live
                 in the States.

01:12:40.662 --> 01:12:44.330
 Well, that's no problem.
 I mean, if you'd like to
 leave me your address.

01:12:44.332 --> 01:12:49.001
       Sure, I live
       in Wilmington, Delaware.

01:12:51.205 --> 01:12:53.338
 WOMAN: Would you have any idea
 how long it might take?

01:12:53.340 --> 01:12:57.308
 BILL: It depends
 if we can find one
 through our usual contacts,

01:12:57.310 --> 01:12:59.576
 maybe a couple of weeks.

01:12:59.578 --> 01:13:01.110
 WOMAN: Oh, that would be fine.

01:13:01.112 --> 01:13:03.479
  <i> FRANK: "Had I the heavens'</i>
  <i> embroidered cloths</i>

01:13:03.481 --> 01:13:07.649
      <i> "Enwrought with golden</i>
      <i> and silver light</i>

01:13:07.784 --> 01:13:10.651
  <i> "The blue and the dim</i>
  <i> and the dark cloths</i>

01:13:10.653 --> 01:13:14.254
  <i> "Of night and light</i>
  <i> and the half light</i>

01:13:14.256 --> 01:13:17.757
  <i> "I would spread the cloths</i>
  <i> under your feet</i>

01:13:17.759 --> 01:13:21.927
  <i> "But I, being poor,</i>
  <i> have only my dreams</i>

01:13:21.929 --> 01:13:25.597
  <i> "I have spread my dreams</i>
  <i> under your feet</i>

01:13:25.599 --> 01:13:31.236
  <i> "Tread softly because</i>
  <i> you tread on my dreams"</i>

01:13:34.574 --> 01:13:35.940
          (CRASHING)

01:13:35.942 --> 01:13:38.842
 Hey, what the hell
 are you doing?

01:13:38.844 --> 01:13:41.377
               I'm minding
               my own business.

01:13:41.379 --> 01:13:43.045
            What are you doing?

01:13:43.047 --> 01:13:46.815
 You can't do that!
 Put that light back!

01:13:46.817 --> 01:13:48.016
          Who says?

01:13:48.018 --> 01:13:49.917
 I say and I live here!

01:13:49.919 --> 01:13:52.586
 Not for much longer, lady.

01:13:59.161 --> 01:14:03.997
    <i> HELENE: "Dear Frank.</i>
    <i> The sky fell on us</i>
    <i> in this cozy brownstone.</i>

01:14:03.999 --> 01:14:05.898
     <i> "We got eviction notices</i>
     <i> last month.</i>

01:14:05.900 --> 01:14:07.399
       <i> "They're renovating</i>
       <i> the building.</i>

01:14:07.401 --> 01:14:12.203
<i> "They decided the time had</i>
<i> come for me to get a real</i>
<i> apartment with real furniture.</i>

01:14:12.205 --> 01:14:15.372
      <i> "And in my right mind</i>
      <i> and shaking all over</i>

01:14:15.374 --> 01:14:16.639
     <i> "I went around</i>
     <i> to the construction site</i>

01:14:16.641 --> 01:14:19.341
  <i> "of the new building going up</i>
  <i> over on Second Avenue</i>

01:14:19.343 --> 01:14:25.447
     <i> "and signed a lease</i>
     <i> on a two and a half</i>
     <i> bed-sitter apartment.</i>

01:14:25.449 --> 01:14:28.049
  <i> "That isn't even there yet."</i>

01:14:34.957 --> 01:14:36.356
          (BELLS RINGING)

01:14:36.358 --> 01:14:40.593
  <i> FRANK: "Dear Helene.</i>
  <i> Prepare yourself for a shock.</i>

01:14:41.162 --> 01:14:44.396
    <i> "All three of the books</i>
    <i> that you requested</i>
    <i> in your last letter</i>

01:14:44.398 --> 01:14:48.533
    <i> "are on their way to you</i>
    <i> and should arrive</i>
    <i> in a week or so.</i>

01:14:48.535 --> 01:14:50.268
          <i> "Don't ask how</i>
          <i> we managed it.</i>

01:14:50.270 --> 01:14:53.371
      <i> "It's just part</i>
      <i> of the Marks' service."</i>

01:14:53.373 --> 01:14:58.309
 <i> MAN ON TV: Times Square</i>
 <i> is jammed with jubilant</i>
 <i> New Yorkers and visitors.</i>

01:14:58.311 --> 01:15:01.145
  <i> But they are celebrating</i>
  <i> the New Year.</i>

01:15:01.147 --> 01:15:06.617
 <i> The bright lights of Broadway</i>
 <i> shining on nearly</i>
 <i> a million festive folks.</i>

01:15:06.619 --> 01:15:11.722
    (TYPEWRITER CLACKING)
  <i> The sign of the times.</i>
  <i> Happy New Year!</i>

01:15:13.492 --> 01:15:19.295
     <i> HELENE: "Sunday night</i>
     <i> and a hell of a way</i>
     <i> to start 1960.</i>

01:15:19.297 --> 01:15:20.429
     <i> "I don't know, Frank.</i>

01:15:20.431 --> 01:15:23.198
     <i> "Somebody gave me</i>
     <i> this book for Christmas.</i>

01:15:23.200 --> 01:15:25.600
       <i> "It's a great</i>
       <i> Modern Library book.</i>

01:15:25.602 --> 01:15:27.301
        <i> "Did you ever see</i>
        <i> one of those?</i>

01:15:27.303 --> 01:15:32.906
<i> "It's less attractively bound</i>
<i> than the proceedings</i>
<i> of the New York State Assembly</i>

01:15:32.908 --> 01:15:34.274
      <i> "and it weighs more.</i>

01:15:34.276 --> 01:15:39.512
    <i> "It was given to me</i>
    <i> by a gentleman who knows</i>
    <i> I'm fond of John Donne.</i>

01:15:39.514 --> 01:15:41.213
   <i> "The title of this book is</i>

01:15:41.215 --> 01:15:47.319
     "The Complete Poetry
     and Selected Prose
     of John Donne..."

01:15:47.321 --> 01:15:53.858
        <i> And the Complete Poetry</i>
        <i> of William Blake?</i>

01:15:54.760 --> 01:15:56.993
        <i> "The question mark</i>
        <i> is mine."</i>

01:15:56.995 --> 01:15:59.695
        Will you please tell me
        what those two boys
        have in common,

01:15:59.697 --> 01:16:06.234
   except they were both
   English and they both wrote.

01:16:06.970 --> 01:16:12.673
   "When, as a little boy,
   William Blake saw the
   prophet Ezekiel under a tree

01:16:12.675 --> 01:16:19.079
        "amid a summer field,
        he was soundly trounced
        by his mother."

01:16:19.781 --> 01:16:22.148
          I'm with his mother.
          I mean,

01:16:22.150 --> 01:16:26.285
 the back of the Lord God,
 the face of the Virgin Mary,
 all right.

01:16:26.287 --> 01:16:32.924
           Why the hell would
           anybody want to see
           the prophet Ezekiel?

01:16:34.193 --> 01:16:39.896
    <i> "But the crucial word</i>
    <i> in all that is 'selected.'</i>

01:16:39.898 --> 01:16:44.867
       <i> "The selected prose</i>
       <i> of John Donne?</i>

01:16:46.170 --> 01:16:47.202
     <i> (CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING</i>
     <i> ON RADIO)</i>

01:16:47.204 --> 01:16:51.639
  <i> "Here I was</i>
  <i> curled up in my armchair,</i>
  <i> so at peace with the world,</i>

01:16:51.641 --> 01:16:54.208
     <i> "with something old</i>
     <i> and serene on the radio,</i>

01:16:54.210 --> 01:16:59.546
   <i> "Corelli or somebody,</i>
   <i> and this thing on the table.</i>

01:16:59.548 --> 01:17:04.183
      <i> "This giant</i>
      <i> Modern Library thing.</i>

01:17:04.185 --> 01:17:10.455
    <i> "So I thought, I will read</i>
    <i> one of the sermons aloud.</i>

01:17:10.457 --> 01:17:13.024
<i> "You have to read Donne aloud.</i>

01:17:13.693 --> 01:17:16.293
    <i> "It's like a Bach fugue."</i>

01:17:25.737 --> 01:17:28.971
    "All mankind is one volume.

01:17:29.406 --> 01:17:34.475
          "When one man dies,
          one chapter is not
          torn out of the book,

01:17:34.477 --> 01:17:39.279
           "but translated into
           a better language.

01:17:39.814 --> 01:17:44.983
         "And every chapter
         must be so translated.

01:17:44.985 --> 01:17:48.186
           "God employs
           several translators.

01:17:48.188 --> 01:17:51.756
         "Some pieces
         are translated by age,

01:17:52.091 --> 01:17:55.725
             "some by sickness,

01:17:55.927 --> 01:17:57.359
                "some by war,

01:18:00.163 --> 01:18:01.962
        "some by justice.

01:18:03.065 --> 01:18:04.597
 "But God's hand shall bind up

01:18:04.599 --> 01:18:10.169
 "all our scattered leaves
 again for that library

01:18:10.171 --> 01:18:15.240
        "where every book
        shall lie open
        to one another."

01:18:24.818 --> 01:18:33.291
      <i> "Dizzy with Donne,</i>
      <i> I craved for more</i>
      <i> but the closet was bare.</i>

01:18:33.693 --> 01:18:36.560
    <i> "Selected prose, remember?</i>

01:18:36.562 --> 01:18:37.494
   <i> "So break it to me gently.</i>

01:18:37.496 --> 01:18:42.098
  <i> "How hard is it going to be</i>
  <i> to find the great man's</i>
  <i> complete sermons</i>

01:18:42.100 --> 01:18:44.867
       <i> "and how much is it</i>
       <i> going to cost?"</i>

01:18:50.708 --> 01:18:56.878
     You know, Frankie,
     you're the only soul alive
     who understands me.

01:19:06.890 --> 01:19:07.655
      <i> FRANK: "Dear Helene.</i>

01:19:07.657 --> 01:19:13.961
  <i> "Some time ago, you asked me</i>
  <i> for a modern version of</i>
  <i> Chaucer's</i> Canterbury Tales.

01:19:13.963 --> 01:19:16.296
 <i> "I came across a little volume</i>
 <i> the other day</i>

01:19:16.298 --> 01:19:18.231
         <i> "which I thought</i>
         <i> you would like.</i>

01:19:18.233 --> 01:19:20.600
       <i> "It is not complete</i>
       <i> by any means.</i>

01:19:20.602 --> 01:19:23.002
        <i> "But as it is</i>
        <i> quite a cheap book</i>

01:19:23.004 --> 01:19:26.038
     <i> "and seems to be</i>
     <i> a fairly scholarly job,</i>

01:19:26.040 --> 01:19:29.174
      <i> "I am sending it along</i>
      <i> by book post today.</i>

01:19:29.176 --> 01:19:32.043
         <i> "Price: $1.35."</i>

01:19:32.045 --> 01:19:34.245
  Looks very nice.

01:19:34.247 --> 01:19:34.678
                         Good.

01:19:34.680 --> 01:19:38.148
   <i> "We are all well</i>
   <i> and jogging along as usual.</i>

01:19:38.150 --> 01:19:40.183
       <i> "My eldest daughter,</i>
       <i> Sheila, 24,</i>

01:19:40.185 --> 01:19:42.685
   <i> "suddenly decided</i>
   <i> she wanted to be a teacher.</i>

01:19:42.687 --> 01:19:48.624
 <i> "So threw up her</i>
 <i> secretarial job two years ago</i>
 <i> to go to college."</i>

01:19:49.994 --> 01:19:50.559
      Hot gravy.

01:19:50.561 --> 01:19:54.029
  <i> "She has another year to go,</i>
  <i> so it looks as though</i>
  <i> it will be a long time</i>

01:19:54.031 --> 01:19:58.833
     <i> "before our children</i>
     <i> will be able</i>
     <i> to keep us in luxury.</i>

01:19:58.835 --> 01:20:02.236
  <i> "Love from all here. Frank."</i>

01:20:33.602 --> 01:20:36.035
        Very nice.
        Very tasty.

01:20:40.074 --> 01:20:43.775
 It's been 12 years
 since I was in London
 with that play.

01:20:43.777 --> 01:20:44.542
            I don't believe it.

01:20:44.544 --> 01:20:45.809
 It's more than 12 years.
 It was...

01:20:45.811 --> 01:20:48.311
   <i> HELENE:</i>
   <i> "All right, that's enough</i>
   <i> Chaucer-made-easy.</i>

01:20:48.313 --> 01:20:53.916
  <i> "It has the schoolroom smell</i>
  <i> of Lamb's</i> Tales
  from Shakespeare.

01:20:54.084 --> 01:20:54.849
      <i> "I'm glad I read it.</i>

01:20:54.851 --> 01:20:58.319
   <i> "I liked reading about</i>
   <i> the nun who ate so dainty</i>
   <i> with her fingers,</i>

01:20:58.321 --> 01:21:00.888
      <i> "she never dripped</i>
      <i> any grease on herself.</i>

01:21:00.890 --> 01:21:03.557
         <i> "I could never</i>
         <i> make that claim.</i>

01:21:03.559 --> 01:21:08.361
    <i> "Wasn't anything else</i>
    <i> that intrigued me much.</i>
    <i> It's just stories.</i>

01:21:08.363 --> 01:21:09.362
         <i> "Now, if Chaucer</i>
         <i> had kept a diary</i>

01:21:09.364 --> 01:21:13.699
 <i> "and told me what it was like</i>
 <i> to be a little clerk</i>
 <i> in the palace of Richard III,</i>

01:21:13.701 --> 01:21:16.368
         <i> "that, I'd learn</i>
         <i> Old English for.</i>

01:21:16.370 --> 01:21:21.239
   <i> "'The reader will not credit</i>
   <i> that such things could be,'</i>

01:21:21.241 --> 01:21:24.542
      <i> "Walton says somewhere</i>
      <i> or other,</i>

01:21:24.744 --> 01:21:29.213
        <i> "'but I was there</i>
        <i> and I saw it.'</i>

01:21:30.482 --> 01:21:31.414
        <i> "That's for me.</i>

01:21:31.416 --> 01:21:34.517
      <i> "I'm a great lover of</i>
      <i> 'I was there' books."</i>

01:21:34.519 --> 01:21:36.852
 It was a rotten play.

01:21:36.854 --> 01:21:38.253
        I thought you liked it.

01:21:38.255 --> 01:21:40.121
 I hated it.

01:21:41.591 --> 01:21:45.092
             Listen, you should
             be grateful.

01:21:45.094 --> 01:21:47.994
            That play
            took you to London.

01:21:48.429 --> 01:21:51.296
             Remember
             how jealous I was?

01:21:51.931 --> 01:21:53.697
  You were.

01:21:53.932 --> 01:21:55.464
                         I was.

01:22:00.537 --> 01:22:02.003
                        I was.

01:22:06.009 --> 01:22:10.177
      <i> FRANK: "Dear Helene.</i>
      <i> It was good to</i>
      <i> hear from you again.</i>

01:22:10.179 --> 01:22:16.116
   <i> "We're still here,</i>
   <i> getting older and busier,</i>
   <i> but no richer.</i>

01:22:16.118 --> 01:22:20.920
  <i> "We had a pleasant summer</i>
  <i> with more than</i>
  <i> the usual number of tourists</i>

01:22:20.922 --> 01:22:22.588
        <i> "including hordes</i>
        <i> of young people</i>

01:22:22.590 --> 01:22:25.824
      <i> "making the pilgrimage</i>
      <i> to Carnaby Street.</i>

01:22:25.826 --> 01:22:27.759
      <i> "We watch it all</i>
      <i> from a safe distance.</i>

01:22:27.761 --> 01:22:31.162
    <i> "Though I must say,</i>
    <i> I rather like The Beatles.</i>

01:22:31.164 --> 01:22:31.929
    <i> (MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO)</i>

01:22:31.931 --> 01:22:35.465
     <i> "If the fans</i>
     <i> just wouldn't scream so.</i>

01:22:36.501 --> 01:22:40.269
       <i> "We have not heard</i>
       <i> from Cecily Farr</i>
       <i> in some years now.</i>

01:22:40.271 --> 01:22:43.071
    <i> "Megan Wells had enough</i>
    <i> of South Africa</i>
    <i> in a very short time,</i>

01:22:43.073 --> 01:22:48.209
  <i> "and did stop in</i>
  <i> to give us a chance to say,</i>
  <i> 'I told you so,'</i>

01:22:48.211 --> 01:22:51.178
     <i> "before trying her luck</i>
     <i> in Australia."</i>

01:22:51.180 --> 01:22:52.779
 Frank, will you
 lock up?

01:22:52.781 --> 01:22:55.948
       Yes, I will.
       Good night, Bill.

01:22:56.617 --> 01:23:02.487
    <i> "We had a Christmas card</i>
    <i> from her a few years ago</i>
    <i> but nothing recently.</i>

01:23:02.856 --> 01:23:06.891
     <i> "Nora and the girls</i>
     <i> join me in sending love.</i>

01:23:07.526 --> 01:23:09.125
            <i> "Frank."</i>

01:23:24.308 --> 01:23:26.741
     (TYPEWRITER CLACKING)

01:23:30.379 --> 01:23:31.911
                 Frank.

01:23:32.380 --> 01:23:34.079
               You still there?

01:23:36.249 --> 01:23:38.148
           Still alive, are we?

01:23:38.150 --> 01:23:42.452
       I swore I wouldn't write
       until I found work.

01:23:42.620 --> 01:23:45.253
         Sold a story
         to <i> Harper's Magazine.</i>

01:23:45.255 --> 01:23:47.088
              Slaved over it
              for three weeks.

01:23:47.090 --> 01:23:48.489
                  They paid me
                  $200 for it.

01:23:48.491 --> 01:23:53.827
   Now they've got me
   writing the story of my life
   in a book.

01:23:54.429 --> 01:23:56.695
          How about you, Frank?

01:23:58.932 --> 01:23:59.997
             Yes.

01:23:59.999 --> 01:24:03.234
  We're all very much alive
  and kicking,

01:24:03.236 --> 01:24:06.837
    though rather exhausted
    after a hectic summer.

01:24:07.639 --> 01:24:08.738
             Now, listen.

01:24:08.740 --> 01:24:10.072
      I introduced
      a young friend of mine

01:24:10.074 --> 01:24:12.908
       to <i> Pride and Prejudice</i>
       one rainy Sunday.

01:24:12.910 --> 01:24:15.176
   And she's gone out
   of her mind for Jane Austen.

01:24:15.178 --> 01:24:19.346
       She has a birthday
       around about Halloween.

01:24:19.614 --> 01:24:22.982
        Can you find me
        some Austen for her?

01:24:24.552 --> 01:24:25.284
           I know you can.

01:24:25.286 --> 01:24:31.290
 There's no hope of finding any
 Jane Austen in time
 for your friend's birthday.

01:24:31.292 --> 01:24:35.360
 We've had hordes of tourists
 from the USA,

01:24:35.362 --> 01:24:37.862
    France, Scandinavia,
    etcetera,

01:24:37.864 --> 01:24:39.864
    all buying our nice,
    leather-bound books.

01:24:39.866 --> 01:24:42.700
 So our stock is a sorry sight
 at the moment.

01:24:42.702 --> 01:24:45.803
 But perhaps we can find them
 for her for Christmas.

01:24:45.805 --> 01:24:46.770
    Are you a grandfather yet?

01:24:46.772 --> 01:24:51.808
   Tell Sheila and Mary
   their children are entitled
   to presentation copies of

01:24:51.810 --> 01:24:54.610
  my <i> Collected Juvenile Works.</i>

01:24:54.612 --> 01:24:58.714
     That should make them
     rush out and reproduce.

01:24:59.016 --> 01:25:03.385
     Best to Nora
     and anybody else around.

01:25:04.187 --> 01:25:05.553
            Helene.

01:25:05.555 --> 01:25:10.090
 Nora and the girls are fine.
 Sheila is teaching.

01:25:10.092 --> 01:25:12.158
    Mary is engaged
    to a very nice boy.

01:25:12.160 --> 01:25:16.395
 But there is little hope
 of them getting married
 for the time being.

01:25:16.397 --> 01:25:17.529
 As neither has any money.

01:25:17.531 --> 01:25:23.368
 So Nora's hopes of being
 a glamorous grandmother
 are receding fast.

01:25:23.470 --> 01:25:26.170
         Love, Frank.

01:25:31.143 --> 01:25:33.209
        (SIRENS WAILING)

01:25:35.213 --> 01:25:39.415
 <i> MAN ON PA: We have</i>
 <i> hundreds of plainclothesmen</i>
 <i> in our midst.</i>

01:25:39.417 --> 01:25:43.752
    <i> Many of these guys</i>
    <i> have orders</i>
    <i> to beat up the leaders.</i>

01:25:43.754 --> 01:25:47.288
          <i> Now, this is clearly</i>
          <i> a political activity,</i>

01:25:47.290 --> 01:25:51.592
           <i> a political action</i>
           <i> on the part of</i>
           <i> the Administration.</i>

01:25:51.594 --> 01:25:52.826
         Well, they are not
         going to get amnesty.

01:25:52.828 --> 01:25:56.629
          And I think that
          there's going to be
          a solution,

01:25:56.631 --> 01:25:59.131
         so I don't think
         it's going to go on.

01:25:59.133 --> 01:26:00.832
            (SHOUTING)

01:26:02.802 --> 01:26:05.302
     (PROTESTERS CLAMORING)

01:26:21.420 --> 01:26:22.018
     What's going on?

01:26:22.020 --> 01:26:25.388
         Oh, please!
         Back on the other side
         of the cordon, lady.

01:26:25.390 --> 01:26:27.823
 I asked you a civil question.
 What's going on?

01:26:27.825 --> 01:26:30.425
        No demonstrations
        allowed on this campus.

01:26:30.427 --> 01:26:30.858
        Who says?

01:26:30.860 --> 01:26:32.693
              Lady, aren't you
              a little old
              to be doing this?

01:26:32.695 --> 01:26:34.961
          Why don't you go home
          and bake an apple pie
          or something?

01:26:34.963 --> 01:26:38.064
 Why don't you go home
 and bake an apple pie
 or something?

01:26:38.066 --> 01:26:40.666
           All right, lady.
           Make yourself happy.

01:26:40.668 --> 01:26:43.201
        You get to ride in here
        with the rest
        of your friends.

01:26:43.203 --> 01:26:45.169
 HELENE: I want to say
 something. Don't go away!

01:26:45.171 --> 01:26:48.805
       Wait a minute.
       I want to say something.

01:26:48.807 --> 01:26:51.808
           Wait a minute!
           I want to talk to...

01:26:52.377 --> 01:26:54.910
          Let's get them
          the hell out of here!

01:27:27.010 --> 01:27:29.176
  <i> REPORTER: It seems</i>
  <i> there'll be no easy solution</i>

01:27:29.178 --> 01:27:32.779
  <i> to the student sit-in</i>
  <i> on campus at Columbia.</i>

01:27:32.781 --> 01:27:33.913
     <i> MAN: We want to</i>
     <i> point out that,</i>

01:27:33.915 --> 01:27:37.950
  <i> one, that black students</i>
  <i> occupy this building here.</i>

01:27:37.952 --> 01:27:39.885
     <i> And we are going into</i>
     <i> the community of Harlem</i>

01:27:39.887 --> 01:27:41.586
          <i> and bolster</i>
          <i> support down there.</i>

01:27:41.588 --> 01:27:45.122
    <i> So if Columbia</i>
    <i> doesn't want to deal</i>
    <i> with the brothers in here,</i>

01:27:45.124 --> 01:27:47.591
       <i> they'll deal with them</i>
       <i> on the street.</i>

01:27:47.593 --> 01:27:48.558
          <i> (ALL CHEERING)</i>

01:27:48.560 --> 01:27:52.428
    <i> STUDENTS: (CHANTING)</i>
    <i> Strike! Strike!</i>

01:27:53.731 --> 01:27:56.198
     <i> (PROTESTERS CHANTING)</i>

01:28:17.754 --> 01:28:19.220
  <i> HELENE: Meet me</i>
  <i> at the police station!</i>

01:28:19.222 --> 01:28:20.354
  <i> I want to give</i>
  <i> something to you.</i>

01:28:20.356 --> 01:28:22.489
 <i> Don't worry,</i>
 <i> I'm not finished</i>
 <i> with you...</i>

01:28:22.491 --> 01:28:23.957
        <i> OFFICER: Sit down!</i>

01:28:23.959 --> 01:28:25.658
                    (CHUCKLING)

01:28:34.568 --> 01:28:36.000
  <i> REPORTER:</i>
  <i> Why are you here today?</i>

01:28:36.002 --> 01:28:41.105
<i> MAN: Well, we're not concerned</i>
<i> with the sit-ins</i>
<i> themselves or the arrests.</i>

01:28:41.107 --> 01:28:44.174
     <i> We don't think there's any</i>
     <i> civil liberties issues</i>

01:28:44.176 --> 01:28:45.475
           <i> involved</i>
           <i> in arresting people,</i>

01:28:45.477 --> 01:28:51.914
       <i> after they've been</i>
       <i> occupying the buildings</i>
       <i> on an illegal basis.</i>

01:28:55.653 --> 01:28:58.020
    <i> WOMAN: "January 8, 1969.</i>

01:28:58.022 --> 01:28:58.653
          <i> "Dear Miss.</i>

01:28:58.655 --> 01:29:04.792
  <i> "I have just come across</i>
  <i> the letter you wrote to</i>
  <i> Mr. Doel last September 30.</i>

01:29:04.794 --> 01:29:07.261
     <i> "It is with great regret</i>
     <i> that I have to tell you,</i>

01:29:07.263 --> 01:29:10.897
     <i> "that he passed away</i>
     <i> on Sunday, December 22.</i>

01:29:10.899 --> 01:29:15.434
    <i> "The funeral took place</i>
    <i> last week</i>
    <i> on Wednesday, January 1.</i>

01:29:15.436 --> 01:29:18.703
    <i> "He was rushed to hospital</i>
    <i> December 15,</i>

01:29:18.705 --> 01:29:21.706
     <i> "and operated on</i>
     <i> for a ruptured appendix.</i>

01:29:21.708 --> 01:29:24.842
        <i> "Unfortunately,</i>
        <i> peritonitis set in</i>

01:29:24.844 --> 01:29:27.177
<i> "and he died seven days later.</i>

01:29:27.179 --> 01:29:29.946
    <i> "He had been with the firm</i>
    <i> over 40 years.</i>

01:29:29.948 --> 01:29:33.950
  <i> "Naturally,</i>
  <i> it has come as a great shock</i>
  <i> to Mr. Cohen,</i>

01:29:33.952 --> 01:29:38.654
  <i> "particularly coming so soon</i>
  <i> after the death of Mr. Marks.</i>

01:29:38.656 --> 01:29:43.158
     <i> "Do you still wish us</i>
     <i> to obtain the books</i>
     <i> you asked for?</i>

01:29:43.160 --> 01:29:43.892
           (SOBBING)

01:29:43.894 --> 01:29:47.462
        <i> "Yours faithfully,</i>
        <i> P.P. Marks & Co.</i>

01:29:47.464 --> 01:29:51.065
 <i> "Joan Todd, Mrs., Secretary."</i>

01:30:08.484 --> 01:30:09.916
      <i> NORA: "Dear Helene.</i>

01:30:09.918 --> 01:30:13.185
    <i> "Thank you</i>
    <i> for your very kind letter.</i>

01:30:13.187 --> 01:30:15.287
     <i> "Nothing about it at all</i>
     <i> offends me.</i>

01:30:15.289 --> 01:30:21.860
   <i> "I only wish that</i>
   <i> you had met Frank</i>
   <i> and known him personally.</i>

01:30:21.995 --> 01:30:25.296
       <i> "He was the most</i>
       <i> well-adjusted person</i>

01:30:25.298 --> 01:30:28.732
        <i> "with a marvelous</i>
        <i> sense of humor.</i>

01:30:28.734 --> 01:30:31.868
      <i> "And now, I realize,</i>
      <i> such a modest person,</i>

01:30:31.870 --> 01:30:35.304
      <i> "as I've had letters</i>
      <i> from all over</i>
      <i> to pay him tribute.</i>

01:30:35.306 --> 01:30:40.542
  <i> "And so many people</i>
  <i> in the book trade</i>
  <i> say he was so knowledgeable</i>

01:30:40.544 --> 01:30:45.813
  <i> "and imparted his knowledge</i>
  <i> with kindness</i>
  <i> to all and sundry.</i>

01:30:45.815 --> 01:30:49.917
    <i> "If you wish,</i>
    <i> I could send them to you.</i>

01:30:51.186 --> 01:30:57.957
   <i> "At times, I don't mind</i>
   <i> telling you,</i>
   <i> I was very jealous of you,</i>

01:30:58.092 --> 01:30:59.991
     <i> "as Frank</i>
     <i> so enjoyed your letters.</i>

01:30:59.993 --> 01:31:04.962
      <i> "And they, or some,</i>
      <i> were so like</i>
      <i> his sense of humor.</i>

01:31:05.097 --> 01:31:08.798
      <i> "Also, I envied</i>
      <i> your writing ability.</i>

01:31:09.767 --> 01:31:13.635
     <i> "Frank and I were</i>
     <i> so very much opposites.</i>

01:31:14.137 --> 01:31:16.237
    <i> "He so kind and gentle,</i>

01:31:16.239 --> 01:31:18.539
    <i> "and me,</i>
    <i> with my Irish background,</i>

01:31:18.541 --> 01:31:21.675
         <i> "always fighting</i>
         <i> for my rights.</i>

01:31:24.079 --> 01:31:26.112
        <i> "I miss him so.</i>

01:31:26.848 --> 01:31:29.748
   <i> "Life was so interesting.</i>

01:31:29.983 --> 01:31:32.416
     <i> "He, always explaining</i>

01:31:32.418 --> 01:31:36.386
     <i> "and trying to teach me</i>
     <i> something of books.</i>

01:31:38.156 --> 01:31:42.992
     <i> "My girls are wonderful,</i>
     <i> and in this I am lucky.</i>

01:31:43.194 --> 01:31:47.396
    <i> "I suppose so many like me</i>
    <i> are all alone.</i>

01:31:48.065 --> 01:31:50.932
   <i> "Please excuse my scrawl.</i>

01:31:51.167 --> 01:31:53.534
       <i> "With love, Nora."</i>

01:31:59.441 --> 01:32:00.506
  <i> HELENE: "Dear Kay and Brian.</i>

01:32:00.508 --> 01:32:05.077
  <i> "I take time out</i>
  <i> from cleaning my bookshelves</i>
  <i> and sitting on the rug</i>

01:32:05.079 --> 01:32:08.246
       <i> "surrounded by books</i>
       <i> in every direction.</i>

01:32:08.248 --> 01:32:10.414
   <i> "I wish you a bon voyage.</i>

01:32:10.416 --> 01:32:13.517
      <i> "I hope you and Brian</i>
      <i> have a ball in London.</i>

01:32:13.519 --> 01:32:16.319
     <i> "Maybe it's just as well</i>
     <i> I never got there.</i>

01:32:16.321 --> 01:32:18.754
       <i> "I dreamed about it</i>
       <i> for so many years.</i>

01:32:18.756 --> 01:32:24.259
  <i> "I used to go to</i>
  <i> English movies</i>
  <i> just to look at the streets.</i>

01:32:24.761 --> 01:32:28.095
    <i> "Years ago, a guy I knew</i>
    <i> told me that</i>
    <i> people going to England</i>

01:32:28.097 --> 01:32:31.264
    <i> "find exactly</i>
    <i> what they go looking for.</i>

01:32:31.266 --> 01:32:35.167
     <i> "I said I'd go looking</i>
     <i> for the England</i>
     <i> of English literature.</i>

01:32:35.169 --> 01:32:39.304
       <i> "He nodded and said,</i>
       <i> 'It's there.'</i>

01:32:40.940 --> 01:32:44.141
       <i> "Maybe it is</i>
       <i> and maybe it isn't.</i>

01:32:44.143 --> 01:32:48.311
     <i> "Looking around the rug,</i>
     <i> one thing's for sure.</i>

01:32:49.814 --> 01:32:51.747
          <i> "It's here.</i>

01:32:55.652 --> 01:33:01.222
    <i> "The blessed man</i>
    <i> who sold me all my books</i>
    <i> died a few months ago.</i>

01:33:01.224 --> 01:33:05.559
   <i> "And Mr. Marks,</i>
   <i> who owned the shop, is dead.</i>

01:33:06.161 --> 01:33:08.261
         <i> "But Marks & Co.</i>
         <i> is still there,</i>

01:33:08.263 --> 01:33:11.931
   <i> "though there's some talk</i>
   <i> that it might be demolished.</i>

01:33:11.933 --> 01:33:13.899
          <i> "God forbid!</i>

01:33:16.737 --> 01:33:21.740
     <i> "If you happen to</i>
     <i> pass by</i>
     <i> 84 Charing Cross Road,</i>

01:33:21.742 --> 01:33:23.374
        <i> "kiss it for me!</i>

01:33:23.376 --> 01:33:25.809
      <i> "I owe it so much."</i>

01:34:29.140 --> 01:34:30.005
            Hello.

01:34:30.007 --> 01:34:35.110
     I have a brochure
     from a long time ago
     for trips to London.

01:34:35.112 --> 01:34:37.445
   I know they don't cost
   $359 anymore,

01:34:37.447 --> 01:34:42.316
  but could you let me know
  what it would cost?

01:34:43.252 --> 01:34:44.751
              Now?

01:35:20.421 --> 01:35:22.888
           Here I am, Frankie.

01:35:23.123 --> 01:35:25.223
        I finally made it.
